snippet.textDisplay:
No change from Emery.... We played 4 - 2 - 3 -1 or in three layers 4 - 5 - 1. This is a
pessimistic formation. There is no counter attack because the target is a
single man up top that is easily covered. So the attack is consistent
and predictable having no explosive counter. Two defensive midfielders
in front of our back line crowd the defensive line's ability to
determine at what point committing to an attack should happen. This in
turn, stifles our defensive cover of the commitment through overlapping.
By equally spacing out every player over the whole pitch every space is
occupied therefore crowding the pitch. As any player moving into an
open space then will crowd another space. Crowded space is easily
covered by the opposition. All they have to do is stand there. This is
the strategy that Emery began and employed. So there was no change from
Emery. Pepe coming on late as a surprise substitution is something that
Freddie was leaning towards. I think I was would rather build a strong
lead than get a surprise victory with 10 min left in the match. Freddie
is a layered formation type of guy as well. So there has been no change.
This means that Arteta is not in control of the choices with the team.
